Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Was staying nearby and we stopped to look at the menu outside and they came out to tell us about the specials for the night as well. We had the Sliptong and Steak specials. Both were cooked perfectly and delicious. Had a couple drinks and dessert as well. Was a nice intimate atmosphere and very enjoyable. Would recommend highly.

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Straightforward clean and unfussy menu, changes often enough to be able to try most things before moving on to the new selection, as well as the specials board. Nice decor, small with a comfortable atmosphere, but light and bright so one …

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Really great find in Amsterdam! Right off the beaten tourist track, but so much better than the larger eateries around it. Looks like a converted house that feels really cozy. The food is served in generous portions, and it is truly outstanding! Try baked eggplant appetizer with honey and goat cheese.... Amazing!

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Loved the atmosphere, cute little place tucked just out of the way of the crowds. Very friendly and helpful waitress. They had more than just the boring vegetarian basics to choose from, and the lasagne special I had was delicious

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Really great food tucked away down a small street. We had the Dutch snacks which were a great winter warmer, then some pasta cooked better than most Italians!

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Really friendly staff and a good atmosphere, it's also nice to sit outside if the weather's good. If it gets cold they put out blankets and the food is amazing for meat-eaters and vegetarians. Also it's very close to Rembrandt Square. Would recommend.

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Had the French onion soup, it was unique and delicious! All the other food was equally well done, our waitress was wonderful! A good pick for amsterdam where there are lots of choices

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Make yourself a favor a come to eat here. Service is warm, place is great and food is worth every euro. I suggest the Steak of Lamb and the Dutch Fried Snacks. Ask also for a Brouwerij’tij beer

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe

Review Text: I was on a trip to Amsterdam, and I just expected to find a polish restaurant, but I saw everything else but polish food. I will not except this situation. I am so deeply hurt, that I will never come to Amsterdam again.

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
Review Text: Great, intimate little pub restaurant in one of Amsterdam's side streets. Service was great and the food delicious. Would highly recommend.

Name: Szmulewicz Cafe
